  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Ball Jacks is a 1993 game for the Sega Mega Drive by Namco released exclusively in Japan and Europe. The game is a \"sports game\" with a unique sport involving grabbing balls from a conveyor belt on end end of the screen and dropping them into another. Whether or not this is a renamed port of another game is presently unknown.",
